Finance Minister Tito Mboweni responds to questions by MPs after delivering a sobering medium-term budget yesterday. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. CAPE TOWN - Finance Minister Tito Mboweni delivered a sobering medium-term budget on Wednesday. On Thursday, he will respond to questions on his mini-budget in Parliament. READ: SA drowning in debt: Mboweni Mboweni said this year the national debt exceeded R3-trillion and it is expected to rise to R4,5-trillion in the next three years. The minister said state-owned entities need to wean themselves off the national budget.